Object_Heading	Object_Text	aRequirementObjectType	Section_number	ID.Status	aResponsibility	a_EB_PO_Status	a_ZF_PO_Status
1 Performance			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
1.1 Performance Requirements			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The application shall load a project file with up to 500 tasks in under 5 seconds on a Windows 10 desktop with a mid-range CPU.	non functional requirement	1.1.1	PO-NFR-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Gantt Chart scroll and zoom operations shall be smooth with no perceptible lag (< 50 ms repaint) for projects with up to 500 tasks.	non functional requirement	1.1.2	PO-NFR-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Team Planner shall render without lag for up to 50 resources and 500 tasks.	non functional requirement	1.1.3	PO-NFR-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
2 Platform and Technology			2	2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
2.1 Platform and Technology Requirements			2.1	2_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The application shall require Python 3.9 or later.	non functional requirement	2.1.1	PO-NFR-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall require PyQt5 5.15 or later.	non functional requirement	2.1.2	PO-NFR-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall require JPype1 1.4 or later.	non functional requirement	2.1.3	PO-NFR-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall require MPXJ 16.0 or later (Java library).	non functional requirement	2.1.4	PO-NFR-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall require OpenJDK 17. The launcher (cli.bat) shall detect or download it automatically into tools/java/.	non functional requirement	2.1.5	PO-NFR-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
3 Security			3	3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
3.1 Security Requirements			3.1	3_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Credentials stored in KeePass shall never be written to log files, settings files (QSettings), or debug dumps.	non functional requirement	3.1.1	PO-NFR-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall not transmit any project data to external services unless explicitly initiated by the user (e.g. Confluence sync).	non functional requirement	3.1.2	PO-NFR-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall validate all file paths before opening to prevent path traversal vulnerabilities.	non functional requirement	3.1.3	PO-NFR-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
4 Usability			4	4_Heading.0	Not relevant		
4.1 Usability Requirements			4.1	4_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The application shall present a consistent Microsoft Project Pro look-and-feel using an Office blue toolbar/ribbon, light-blue table headers, and Segoe UI fonts.	non functional requirement	4.1.1	PO-NFR-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	All primary operations shall be accessible via both the ribbon and keyboard shortcuts.	non functional requirement	4.1.2	PO-NFR-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall display context-sensitive Edit menu labels that update based on the active tab (e.g. 'Insert Task' vs 'Insert Resource').	non functional requirement	4.1.3	PO-NFR-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
5 Maintainability			5	5_Heading.0	Not relevant		
5.1 Maintainability Requirements			5.1	5_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	View-specific logic shall be encapsulated in separate view classes (task_view.py, gantt_view.py, etc.) following the architecture described in documentation/architecture.md.	non functional requirement	5.1.1	PO-NFR-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	All persistent settings shall be managed exclusively via SettingsManager (QSettings wrapper), ensuring a single point of settings access.	non functional requirement	5.1.2	PO-NFR-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Integration modules (KeePass, Confluence) shall reside in src/integrations/ as independently testable modules.	non functional requirement	5.1.3	PO-NFR-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
6 Deployment			6	6_Heading.0	Not relevant		
6.1 Deployment Requirements			6.1	6_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The application launcher (cli.bat) shall detect or download OpenJDK 17 into tools/java/ on first run using tools/download_openjdk.py.	non functional requirement	6.1.1	PO-NFR-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application launcher (cli.bat) shall detect or download Git for Windows into tools/git/ on first run using tools/download_git_for_windows.py.	non functional requirement	6.1.2	PO-NFR-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application launcher (cli.bat) shall detect or copy TortoiseSVN binaries into tools/svn/ on first run using tools/copy_tortoisesvn_bin.py.	non functional requirement	6.1.3	PO-NFR-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application launcher (cli.bat) shall detect or download the Inno Setup compiler (ISCC.exe) into tools/innosetup/ on first run using tools/download_innosetup.py, fetching the latest release from github.com/jrsoftware/issrc.	non functional requirement	6.1.4	PO-NFR-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application launcher (cli.bat) shall set up a Python virtual environment and install all dependencies from requirements.txt on first run.	non functional requirement	6.1.5	PO-NFR-022.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The standalone executable shall bundle Python runtime, OpenJDK 17, MPXJ, and all Python dependencies. The user shall require no additional software.	non functional requirement	6.1.6	PO-NFR-023.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The standalone build shall be producible via the provided SCons build script (SConstruct) using PyInstaller.	non functional requirement	6.1.7	PO-NFR-024.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The SCons build script shall produce a versioned 7-Zip self-extracting archive (ProjectOffline_<version>.exe) from the dist/ProjectOffline/ bundle; sentinel files (.copied, .bundled) shall be excluded from the archive.	non functional requirement	6.1.8	PO-NFR-025.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The SCons build script shall produce a versioned Inno Setup installer (ProjectOffline_<version>_setup.exe) from the dist/ProjectOffline/ bundle using installer/setup.iss.template as the script source; sentinel files (.copied, .bundled) shall be excluded from the installer package.	non functional requirement	6.1.9	PO-NFR-026.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
</OBJECTS>
